      • calculateHash

        public int calculateHash()
        Description copied from class: IncrementalHasher32
        Method for completing calculation of the hash value for the full byte sequence fed with IncrementalHasher32.update(byte[], int, int). This will NOT reset state, so it is completely legal to feed more content with IncrementalHasher32.update(byte[], int, int), and calculate further hash codes with same instance.

        NOTE: since no state is reset with a call, calling this method typically results in calculation to finalize state. So if you need to access same hash value multiple times, call this method once and retain hash value.

        Specified by:
        calculateHash in class IncrementalHasher32
